---
description: Architecture and dependency boundaries
alwaysApply: true
---

Use Clean Architecture with feature-first organization.

Layers:

- Presentation
- Application
- Domain
- Infrastructure

Dependency direction:

Presentation -> Application -> Domain

Infrastructure implements interfaces defined by Application or Domain.

Rules:

- Presentation must not contain business rules.
- API routers must remain thin.
- Application services orchestrate use cases.
- Domain modules own invariants.
- Infrastructure owns external clients and persistence details.
- Domain code must not import frameworks.
- Avoid cross-domain database access.
- Avoid circular dependencies.
- Keep bounded contexts explicit.
- Use canonical contracts for cross-module communication.
- Prefer events for asynchronous cross-runtime workflows.
- Keep direct side effects isolated.
- No direct agent-to-agent mutation.
- No direct strategy-to-broker access.
- No direct position mutation outside the ledger.

If an architectural boundary must change:

- explain the current boundary,
- explain why it is insufficient,
- compare alternatives,
- propose a migration,
- request approval.
